reviews.text: Surrey's least used station, and mostly useless. It's near the South Downs Way so is good for ramblers, but is on a fairly busy road with no bus service, no car park and no convenient place to pick up and drop off. Betchworth village is not near. It was on Beeching's hit list, but survived because this is Surrey.
Absolutely nothing here. There is a train every two hours on a Sunday but a warning to mind the gap every few minutes. Good base for walking if you can time it right.
